div1.p:
John Winthrop bore an unblemished character.
His virtues were written in every line of his life; he was cultured, yet unassuming;
liberal, yet conservative; gentle, yet firm; politic, yet conscientious; modest, yet courageous; a chivalric gentleman and noble Christian, and his memory deserves to be perpetuated on shaft of adamant, in letters of purest gold.
